  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale dataset)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. The primary experimental dataset used to calibrate blood rheology and hemolysis model constants carries a dataVintage of 2018, predating the modelRevisionDate of 2026. The narrative does not address re-validation against the updated model build, constituting a stale-input epistemic gap (W-EP-03).",
