      "name": "Blood rheology and hemolysis model calibration dataset (2018)",
      "description": "In-vitro measurements of bovine blood viscosity, shear-stress hemolysis thresholds, and power-law exponent fits used to calibrate the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model constants embedded in the CFD solver. Data were collected in 2018 and have not been updated since. The model was rebuilt in January 2026 with revised turbulence coupling, but this calibration dataset was carried forward without re-validation against the new model build.",
      "dataVintage": "2018-03-22T00:00:00Z"
    },
    {
